task.summary: Default task
Added ability to group questions into categories.
Added ability to group questions into categories.
Added unique constraint to the 'category_text' field in the Categories table.
Added ability to filter questions by category.
Allows users to print out PDF after successfully passing quiz.
Users get an email when they have successfully passed a quiz.
Allow users to add multiple videos per quiz
- Refactored code - Need to add tests
- More refactoring - Added required_score to the results page.
- Added the ability to randomize the order of the choices.
- Refactored the email functions
- Added basic functional and unit tests
- Removed the functionality that allows which questions the users answered correctly from the results page.
- Removed unused libraries from email_helpers and helpers
- Users can now print the quiz when they are attempting it
- Users can now print the quiz, before they start taking the quiz.
- Refactored send_success_email - Split saving what quizzes the user completed into a new function called save_user_completion
- Fixing the login issue
- Fixed the login issue

- Added basic file upload capability.
- Added ability to save files on the file system.

- Added ability to allow admins to add files to the quizzes.

- Updated comments.
- Added migration files.
- Minor fixes.

- Modified logic to mark user assigned training as complete. - Modified Completed table.
- Added functionality to remove trainings that have been completed by the user, from the page users can add trainings.
- Added functionality to associate files with videos.

- Users can register and add themselves to groups, to take quizzes.
